			<p>Welcome to my website! My name is Katie and I am currently a junior at Saint Joseph's University in Philadelphia, PA.</p> 
			<p>I am a Communication Studies and Marketing Double Major and anticipate graduating in 2016. My current career goals are to enter into the field of Public Relations or Advertising. My time here has been anything but boring! From the start of freshman year, I have been involved in numerous organizations on and off campus. I was selected to be the Vice President of Communications and Advertising for the American Marketing Association. I attended the annual International Collegiate Conference, where my work during the 2013 term was awarded Outstanding Communications. I was a member of the Peer Educators for the Wellness, Alcohol Drug and Education Office. We educated the Saint Joe's community about healthy lifestyle choices/habits and gave informative presentations to multiple organizations on campus. I was chosen to be a member of the Spring Concert Committee at the end of my sophomore year. Together we organized the annual student concert by contacting the act, promoting the event and setting up Hagan Arena the day of the event. My sophomore year at SJU also included my initiation into the National Society of Collegiate Scholars. I am also a member of Phi Sigma Sigma International Sorority. I was elected to be PanHellenic Delegate for the 2015 term.I currently work at the SJU Bookstore and at home I work at my local Boys & Girls Club. </p>
